Original `instruction_to_text` mixed four distinct concerns in one ~150-line function (degraded-shape handling, AOI dispatch, opaque-op handling, registry rendering). The diff extracts each into its own function and turns the original into a pure dispatcher: `special = _render_special_forms(node, diagnostics, here)
    if special is not None:
        return special
    if aoi is not None and aoi_mod.is_aoi_op(op):
        return _render_aoi(node, operands, diagnostics, here, aoi=aoi, tag_types=tag_types)
    if op == opcodes.OPAQUE_OP:
        return _render_opaque(node, diagnostics, here)
    return _render_registered(node, op, operands, params, diagnostics, here)`. Each extracted function's body is a verbatim move of the corresponding original block (e.g. `_render_aoi` reproduces the AOI branching logic unchanged, `_render_opaque` reproduces the opaque-op logic unchanged), so this is a faithful SRP-improving decomposition with no new coupling and no logic altered — a real, well-scoped SOLID fix.
